  "prompt": "Which are the most romantic songs in Malayalam?",
  "response": "Malayalam cinema is renowned for its soulful and romantic music, and over the years, several songs have captured the hearts of listeners with their melodious tunes and heartfelt lyrics. Here are some of the most romantic Malayalam songs that are cherished by music lovers:\n\n### Classic Romantic Songs:\n1. **\"Manassinakkare\"** (Manassinakkare, 2003) - Sung by K.J. Yesudas, this song is a timeless romantic melody.\n2. **\"Aarum Kannilum\"** (Mazhavilkavadi, 1989) - A beautiful duet by K.S. Chithra and M.G. Sreekumar.\n3. **\"Oru Vadakkan Veeragatha\"** (Oru Vadakkan Veeragatha, 1989) - K.J. Yesudas and K.S. Chithra's voices create magic in this song.\n4. **\"Ponnambili\"** (Summer in Bethlehem, 1998) - A sweet and romantic song by M.G. Sreekumar and Sujatha Mohan.\n\n### Modern Romantic Songs:\n5. **\"Kanne Kanne\"** (Aradhana, 2006) - A hauntingly beautiful number by Shreya Ghoshal.\n6. **\"Puthiyamugam\"** (Thattathin Marayathu, 2012) - Sung by Shreya Ghoshal and Karthik, this song became an instant hit.\n7. **\"Pakal Iravukal\"** (Artist, 2013) - A soft and romantic melody by Vineeth Sreenivasan and Shweta Mohan.\n8. **\"Kannadi Koodum Kootti\"** (Om Shanti Oshana, 2014) - A romantic duet by K.S. Chithra and Vineeth Sreenivasan.\n\n### Folk-Inspired Romantic Songs:\n9. **\"Manikkachirakulla\"** (Kakkakuyil, 2001) - A playful and romantic song by G. Venugopal and Biju Narayanan.\n10. **\"Kaattinu Kaattinu\"** (Nandanam, 2002) - A soulful song by M.G. Sreekumar that blends romance with folk elements.\n\n### Others:\n11. **\"Chundari Penne\"** (Yathrakarude Shradhakku, 2002) - A light-hearted and romantic song by Afsal and Sujatha Mohan.\n12. **\"Ennullil Kannadi\"** (Kireedam, 2007) - A beautiful romantic number by Karthik and Chithra.\n13. **\"Oru Yathramozhi\"** (Salt N' Pepper, 2011) - A soothing melody by Shreya Ghoshal and Vijay Yesudas.\n14. **\"Cherathukal\"** (Charlie, 2015) - A heartwarming song by P. Jayachandran and K.S. Chithra.\n\nThese songs are not only celebrated for their musical brilliance but also for their ability to evoke deep emotions, making them favorites among Malayalam music enthusiasts. Whether classic or modern, each song carries a unique charm that resonates with listeners.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
